## Entry Point
- `main()` — async `#[tokio::main]`
  - Calls `setup_logging()`
  - Delegates to `grok_cli::cli::app::run()`

## Logging — `setup_logging()`
- ### Log File Path
  - `~/.grok/logs/grok-errors.log`
  - Built via `dirs::home_dir()`
  - Parent dirs created with `fs::create_dir_all`
  - Fallback: `grok-errors.log` (CWD)
- ### EnvFilter
  - Reads `RUST_LOG` env var
  - Default: `warn` when unset
  - Examples
    - `RUST_LOG=warn`
    - `RUST_LOG=grok_cli=debug`
    - `RUST_LOG=info`
- ### Stderr Layer
  - Format: compact, coloured
  - No target, no thread IDs
  - Writer: `std::io::stderr`
- ### File Layer (JSON)
  - Format: JSON lines, no ANSI
  - Includes target, file, line number, thread IDs
  - Writer: `Mutex<File>` (append mode)
  - Error handling
    - Success → full two-sink subscriber
    - Failure → stderr-only + `tracing::warn!`

## Dependencies
- `tokio` — async runtime
- `tracing` — structured logging macros
- `tracing-subscriber`
  - `EnvFilter`
  - `fmt` layer (stderr + file)
  - `SubscriberExt` / `SubscriberInitExt`
- `dirs` — home directory resolution
- `anyhow` — error propagation from `main`
- `std::sync::Mutex` — thread-safe file writer

## Error Handling Strategy
- Log file open failure → graceful degradation
  - Subscriber still initialised (stderr only)
  - Warning emitted after init
- `main()` returns `anyhow::Result<()>`
  - Propagates errors from `run()`